Three years ago: Always good food, great service, and can't beat the outdoor seating. Today: Really miss the old Dwyer's. With the current economic, political, and social climate things are different and I get it. What I don't get is why a down home place like Dwyer's has allowed the service to become sub par. The cafe was not busy this morning and my order was not complicated. The cashier brought my coffee and water. After I finished my first cup I waited about ten minutes (no joke) and asked for more coffee. It was another ten minutes before my waitress took my order. I ordered a spinach omelet with a side of bacon. I got my omelet and it was very tasty! I never got a water refill but I did get coffee. My advice to all businesses right now is to focus on the service. At 25%, 50%, or 75% capacity service should be 100% all the time.
